assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: Mansei Corporation provides electronic products in Japan. The company offers general-purpose electrical machines, machines applying electronics, electric powered machines, machines for power receiving and transforming facilities, various industrial machines, air conditioners and low-temperature machines, facilities for buildings and factories, facilities for houses, lighting facilities, elevators and escalators, semiconductors and electronic devices, information and communication machines, visual equipment, FA and OA systems, and microcomputers and ASIC. It also engages in the system design and software development; and design, execution, and sales of construction work. In addition, the company provides high-density memory, one-chip microcomputers, gate arrays, flexible production systems, related control units, CAD/CAM systems NC, robots for industrial use; drive control units, such as AC servos; inverters; controllers, including sequencers; power distribution units comprising; circuit breakers, transformers, and industrial fans; and rotary machines, such as motors, as well as operates a training school. The company was incorporated in 1947 and is headquartered in Osaka, Japan.
